    dc:description "Figure 15. Shells of Margarya oxytropoides: A, Lake Dianchi, DCXHJ 2, 65.9 mm; B, Lake Dianchi, DCXHJ 44, 53.1 mm; C, Lake Dianchi, DCXHJ 3, 54.1 mm; D, Lake Dianchi, DCHK 41, 62.1 mm; E, Lake Lugu (provided by Liu Ye); F, Lake Dianchi, FG68944, 41.0 mm; G, original figure of Paludina oxytropoides (Heude, 1889); H, juvenile shell, 14.2 mm." ;
