    dc:description "Figure 22. Shells of Tchangmargarya multilabiata sp. nov. from Lake Changhu: A, holotype, male individual, FG594250; B, paratype, male individual, CH 1, 59.2 mm; C, paratype, female individual, CH 2, 52.8 mm; D, paratype, CH 7, 52.4 mm; E, paratype, CH 35, 50.77 mm; F, paratype, five keels variety with totally purple calcareous layers, CHX 1, 53.3 mm; G, inner lip; H, juvenile shell with band, 15.4 mm (provided by Hao Yang)." ;
